In recognition of National Dyslexia Awareness Month, the First Lady and President Trump express their support for individuals living with dyslexia. They emphasize the importance of improving learning environments, promoting innovation in workplaces, and strengthening communities to help these individuals succeed and contribute to the country. Dyslexia affects Americans from various backgrounds and millions of people adapt their routines to overcome this common language-based learning disability. Students, in particular, face challenges with reading and writing due to dyslexia. The President and First Lady express gratitude towards educators, administrators, and parents who tirelessly support children with dyslexia, and they commend students who work hard to overcome their disability and achieve educational success. The article concludes by encouraging efforts to provide future generations affected by dyslexia with more opportunities to contribute to their communities, workplaces, and country.